NAME
       telldir — current location of a named directory stream

SYNOPSIS
       #include <dirent.h>

       long telldir(DIR *dirp);

DESCRIPTION
       The telldir() function shall obtain the current location associated with the directory stream specified by dirp.

       If the most recent operation on the directory stream was a seekdir(), the directory position  returned  from  the  telldir()
       shall be the same as that supplied as a loc argument for seekdir().

RETURN VALUE
       Upon successful completion, telldir() shall return the current location of the specified directory stream.

